id: pm-p5if
title: Deduplicate item/metadata to record widening casts behind a shared toItemRecord helper
description: "pm-mbdu planning slice that survived the pm-why9 dedup pass. ~15-18 homogeneous 'item as unknown as Record<string, unknown>' and 'metadata as unknown as Record<string, unknown>' TYPE-widening casts remain across command + core files (append/close/normalize/get/delete/update-many/claim/list/search/update + history/replay). These are distinct from pm-why9's runtime asRecord guards (which check typeof at runtime). Centralize the ItemMetadata/ItemDocument->Record widening behind a single named, documented, fully-covered helper so the type bridge has one source of truth. Heterogeneous casts (frontMatter/normalized/event/definition/frame/plan/hit/settings) stay as-is. Zero behavior change."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: code-quality,dedup,refactor
