updated_at: "2026-05-25T07:56:23.480Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: A shared helper centralizes item/metadata->Record widening; homogeneous casts replaced; new helper module 100% covered and in vitest include; pnpm build+typecheck green; no behavior change.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: "Added src/core/item/item-record.ts exporting toItemRecord(item: ItemMetadata): Record<string,unknown>; replaced 16 homogeneous item/metadata->Record widening casts across 13 files (append/claim/close/delete/get/list/normalize/search/update-many/update + history/replay). New tests/unit/item-record.spec.ts at 100% coverage; module registered in vitest include. Zero behavior change."
expected_result: Item/metadata->Record widening centralized behind one documented helper; homogeneous casts replaced; new module 100% covered; full gate green; no behavior change.
actual_result: "Done. Full release gate green: build/typecheck/coverage(1740 tests,100%)/static/docs-skills/secret-scan/npx-smoke/dogfood/npm-pack/compatibility/sentry-telemetry all pass. Manual temp-dir dogfood exercised get --fields/claim/update/append/list/search/history/normalize/close/delete - all toItemRecord paths working."
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T07:25:18.904Z",cast-dedup-agent,"Centralized homogeneous ItemMetadata/ItemFrontMatter -> Record<string,unknown> widening casts behind one helper. ZERO behavior change.\n\nHELPER: src/core/item/item-record.ts\n  export function toItemRecord(item: ItemMetadata): Record<string, unknown>\n  Single param type ItemMetadata suffices for ALL in-scope sites: ItemFrontMatter is an alias of ItemMetadata (types.ts:475), ListedItem = ItemFrontMatter | (ItemFrontMatter & {body:string}) (both arms assignable), and every ItemDocument site actually casts document.metadata / canonical.metadata (statically ItemMetadata), so no second toItemDocumentRecord helper was needed. Compile-time-only widening (returns same ref); documented as distinct from runtime asRecord* guards in core/shared/primitives.ts.\n\nSITES CHANGED (16 cast sites across 13 source files, all now toItemRecord(...)):\n- src/cli/commands/append.ts (1: result.item)\n- src/cli/commands/delete.ts (1: result.item)\n- src/cli/commands/claim.ts (2: runClaim + runRelease result.item)\n- src/cli/commands/close.ts (1: result.item)\n- src/cli/commands/normalize.ts (1: item ListedItem)\n- src/cli/commands/get.ts (1: item ItemFrontMatter)\n- src/cli/commands/update-many.ts (1: item ListedItem)\n- src/cli/commands/list.ts (1: item ListedItem)\n- src/cli/commands/search.ts (2: the two hit.item casts; the hit-as-record cast at line ~1155 LEFT alone, heterogeneous SearchHit)\n- src/cli/commands/update.ts (4: document.metadata noop, metadataRecord, applyRegisteredItemFieldDefaultsAndValidation arg, result.item)\n- src/core/history/history.ts (2: canonicalHashDocument + canonicalPatchDocument canonical.metadata)\n- src/core/history/replay.ts (1: toReplayDocument canonical.metadata)\n\nSKIPPED (out of scope per coordinator):\n- create.ts:1821 frontMatter (heterogeneous), plan.ts:275 plan (PlanResultPlan), search.ts hit (SearchHit), settings.ts normalizedSettings, schema/item-types-file.ts definition, sentry/instrument.ts frame, all item-format.ts casts (normalized/event/frontMatter) -- item-format.ts is explicitly excluded by scope even though its two frontMatter casts at 1056/1102 are statically ItemMetadata; left untouched to respect the file boundary. update.ts single casts (document.metadata as Record<...>) at ~1909/1912 are NOT double-widening casts, left as-is.\n\nCOVERAGE WIRING:\n- Added src/core/item/item-record.ts to vitest.config.ts coverage include list (next to item-format.ts). Not added to exclude (tiny pure module, fully covered). Confirmed release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts guard 'keeps vitest coverage include list aligned with src ts modules' still passes (module is registered, not flagged uncovered).\n- New spec tests/unit/item-record.spec.ts (3 tests: same-reference identity, field access, mutation-through-reference). Focused coverage: Statements 100% (1/1), Branches 100% (0/0), Functions 100% (1/1), Lines 100% (1/1).\n\nVERIFICATION (all green):\n- pnpm typecheck (tsc --noEmit + tsc packages): EXIT 0\n- pnpm build (tsc): EXIT 0\n- node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- (14 unit specs: item-record, update-command, update-many-command, get-append-command, close-command, delete-command, claim-command, normalize-command, list-command, list-sort-branches, search-command, history-replay, history-activity-command, history-repair-command): 14 files / 207 tests passed\n- node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts: 2 files / 107 tests passed\n\nLeft pm-p5if claimed/in_progress for coordinator to close after the integrated gate."
  "2026-05-25T07:56:23.474Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #65 review response (Gemini, medium): update.ts re-called toItemRecord(document.metadata) at the registered-field validation site while the mutate() callback already holds metadataRecord (same widened reference, never reassigned). Reused metadataRecord there AND at the 4 sibling '(document.metadata as Record<string,unknown>)' index casts (lines ~1898/1901/1910/1913) for consistency, removing 5 more inline casts. Left line 1470 (item: toItemRecord(document.metadata)) untouched since it is outside the callback scope. Build + update-command + cli.integration green."
close_reason: Shipped cast-dedup helper; zero behavior change; full release gate + manual dogfood green.
